 907:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c **** 
 908:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c **** 
 909:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c **** /**
 910:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  * @brief
 911:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  ****************************************************************************************
 912:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *
 913:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *                         I2C State Monitoring Functions
 914:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *                       
 915:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  ****************************************************************************************   
 916:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  * This I2C driver provides three different ways for I2C state monitoring
 917:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *  depending on the application requirements and constraints:
 918:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *        
 919:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *  
 920:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  * 1) Basic state monitoring:
 921:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *    Using I2C_CheckEvent() function:
ARM GAS  C:\Users\ADMIN\AppData\Local\Temp\ccduPF14.s 			page 40


 922:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *    It compares the status registers (SR1 and SR2) content to a given event
 923:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *    (can be the combination of one or more flags).
 924:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *    It returns SUCCESS if the current status includes the given flags 
 925:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *    and returns ERROR if one or more flags are missing in the current status.
 926:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *    - When to use:
 927:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *      - This function is suitable for most applications as well as for startup 
 928:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *      activity since the events are fully described in the product reference manual 
 929:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *      (RM0008).
 930:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *      - It is also suitable for users who need to define their own events.
 931:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *    - Limitations:
 932:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *      - If an error occurs (ie. error flags are set besides to the monitored flags),
 933:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *        the I2C_CheckEvent() function may return SUCCESS despite the communication
 934:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *        hold or corrupted real state. 
 935:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *        In this case, it is advised to use error interrupts to monitor the error
 936:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *        events and handle them in the interrupt IRQ handler.
 937:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *        
 938:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *        @note 
 939:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *        For error management, it is advised to use the following functions:
 940:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *          - I2C_ITConfig() to configure and enable the error interrupts (I2C_IT_ERR).
 941:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *          - I2Cx_ER_IRQHandler() which is called when the error interrupt occurs.
 942:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *            Where x is the peripheral instance (I2C1, I2C2 ...)
 943:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *          - I2C_GetFlagStatus() or I2C_GetITStatus() to be called into I2Cx_ER_IRQHandler() 
 944:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *            in order to determine which error occured.
 945:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *          - I2C_ClearFlag() or I2C_ClearITPendingBit() and/or I2C_SoftwareResetCmd()
 946:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *            and/or I2C_GenerateStop() in order to clear the error flag and source,
 947:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *            and return to correct communication status.
 948:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *            
 949:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *
 950:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *  2) Advanced state monitoring:
 951:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *     Using the function I2C_GetLastEvent() which returns the image of both status 
 952:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *     registers in a single word (uint32_t) (Status Register 2 value is shifted left 
 953:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *     by 16 bits and concatenated to Status Register 1).
 954:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *     - When to use:
 955:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *       - This function is suitable for the same applications above but it allows to
 956:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *         overcome the mentioned limitation of I2C_GetFlagStatus() function.
 957:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *         The returned value could be compared to events already defined in the 
 958:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *         library (stm32f10x_i2c.h) or to custom values defined by user.
 959:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *       - This function is suitable when multiple flags are monitored at the same time.
 960:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *       - At the opposite of I2C_CheckEvent() function, this function allows user to
 961:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *         choose when an event is accepted (when all events flags are set and no 
 962:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *         other flags are set or just when the needed flags are set like 
 963:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *         I2C_CheckEvent() function).
 964:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *     - Limitations:
 965:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *       - User may need to define his own events.
 966:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *       - Same remark concerning the error management is applicable for this 
 967:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *         function if user decides to check only regular communication flags (and 
 968:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *         ignores error flags).
 969:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *     
 970:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *
 971:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *  3) Flag-based state monitoring:
 972:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *     Using the function I2C_GetFlagStatus() which simply returns the status of 
 973:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *     one single flag (ie. I2C_FLAG_RXNE ...). 
 974:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *     - When to use:
 975:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *        - This function could be used for specific applications or in debug phase.
 976:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *        - It is suitable when only one flag checking is needed (most I2C events 
 977:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *          are monitored through multiple flags).
 978:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *     - Limitations: 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\ADMIN\AppData\Local\Temp\ccduPF14.s 			page 41


 979:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *        - When calling this function, the Status register is accessed. Some flags are
 980:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *          cleared when the status register is accessed. So checking the status
 981:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *          of one Flag, may clear other ones.
 982:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *        - Function may need to be called twice or more in order to monitor one 
 983:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *          single event.
 984:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *
 985:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *  For detailed description of Events, please refer to section I2C_Events in 
 986:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *  stm32f10x_i2c.h file.
 987:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  *  
 988:Libraries/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****  */
